1694 /// Returns true if we can statically tell that this value will never be a
1695 /// "useful" constant.  In practice, this means we've got something like an
1696 /// alloca or a malloc call for which a comparison against a constant can
1697 /// only be guarding dead code.  Note that we are potentially giving up some
1698 /// precision in dead code (a constant result) in favour of avoiding a
1699 /// expensive search for a easily answered common query.
